HEADWORD: mol
<hw>mol</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A quantity of a
substance equal to the molecular weight of a substance expressed in
grams; a gram molecule; the basic unit of amount of substance adopted
under the System International d'Unites; <as>as, he added two
<ex>mols</ex> of dextrose to the medium</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gram molecule, mole.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

